Nearly a week after Tropical Cyclone Idai walloped the coast before churning inland, the full extent of the damage is still unclear.
Filipe Nyusi, the president, described seeing bodies floating in rivers as he flew over the region by helicopter.
Schools and hospitals along with bridges and roads need repair.
The Red Cross Red Crescent Climate Centre says that although there were good forecasts of the cyclone, the flooding and landslides it caused were less well anticipated.
Low-lying coastal cities such as Beira are especially vulnerable to storms, which could worsen as climate change disrupts weather patterns.